  - rocm
  - flash-attention-2
abstract: >
  CyberSecQwen-4B is a 4B-parameter language model fine-tuned from
  Qwen3-4B-Instruct-2507 for CWE classification and cyber threat intelligence
  multiple-choice tasks. Trained, merged, and evaluated end-to-end on a single
  AMD Instinct MI300X 192 GB instance via ROCm + vLLM + FlashAttention-2.
  Under Cisco's Foundation-Sec evaluation protocol (arXiv:2504.21039), it
  retains 97.3% of Foundation-Sec-Instruct-8B's CTI-RCM accuracy at half the
  parameter count, while exceeding its CTI-MCQ by +8.7 points (5-trial mean).
  Companion model Gemma4Defense-2B trained with the same recipe on
  Gemma-4-E2B-it converges to within 0.9 points on CTI-RCM, demonstrating
  recipe portability across model families.
